</ul>
<p><a name="Controversy_regarding_use_of_findings" id="Controversy_regarding_use_of_findings"></a></p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline">Controversy regarding use of findings</span></h3>
<ul>
<li>Campell, Robert. "Citations of shame;scientists are still trading on Nazi atrocities.", <a href="/wiki/New_Scientist" title="New Scientist">New Scientist</a>, <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1985-02-28"><a href="/wiki/February_28" title="February 28">28 February</a> <a href="/wiki/1985" title="1985">1985</a></span>, 105(1445), pp.31.<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=11655677&amp;dopt=Abstract" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&amp;db=PubMed&amp;list_uids=11655677&amp;dopt=Abstract" rel="nofollow">[1]</a><a href="http://www.medscape.com/medline/abstract/11655677" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.medscape.com/medline/abstract/11655677" rel="nofollow">[2]</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.garfield.library.upenn.edu/essays/v14p328y1991.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.garfield.library.upenn.edu/essays/v14p328y1991.pdf" rel="nofollow">Citing Nazi ‘Research’: To Do So Without Condemnation Is Not Defensible</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.geocities.com/pennpuab/foundations/naziresearch.html" class="external text" title="http://www.geocities.com/pennpuab/foundations/naziresearch.html" rel="nofollow">On the Ethics of Citing Nazi Research</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.garfield.library.upenn.edu/essays/v8p265y1985.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.garfield.library.upenn.edu/essays/v8p265y1985.pdf" rel="nofollow">Remembering the Holocaust, Part 2</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.jlaw.com/Articles/NaziMedEx.html" class="external text" title="http://www.jlaw.com/Articles/NaziMedEx.html" rel="nofollow">The Ethics Of Using Medical Data From Nazi Experiments</a></li>
</ul>


